│ happens because `deadargelim` changes the return type of `@F38` in its function            │
│ definition, but the `call` instruction inside `@F36` is not correctly updated, leading to  │
│ a type mismatch.\n2.  `musttail call must precede a ret with an optional bitcast`: This is │
│ the more critical error. It confirms our hypothesis that after the transformation, the new │
